"The World Class flavor profile is quite intense, very complex and reasonably balanced.  It begins with a slam of grapefruit that slowly takes on a pine character.  As the hop flavor fades, the rich biscuit and honey sweetness comes to the forefront.  In the middle, a mild bitterness takes the lead.  A blend of the above slowly fade and jostle for prominence going into the finish. The finish is a slow fade of honey over pine bitterness, with grapefruit notes quite evident, and just a touch of alcohol flavor.  The alcohol coverage is simply a brewing masterpiece."
