"Pours an orange amber color, carbonation can be seen rising in the body. There is just a slight haziness. The head stands about one finger tall and is an off white color. Smell is of grapefruit, pineapple, and a slight malt sweetness. Taste has a strong bitterness, I get flavors of citrus: pineapple and grapefruit. I also get some honey, malt sweetness and a touch of alcohol. Mouthfeel is thickish, which is expected. This is a great DIPA."
